Darin,
I have seen duplicates of this defect several times in the past three weeks.
I personally haven't been able to reproduce it.  Looking at the code, I can't 
figure out a situation in which the line in question throws a null pointer 
exception.
Could you please tell me the exact steps that you did to get the exception?

In the Eclipse toolbar, click to realized the debug drop down menu.
Select "Debug..."
NullPointerException

I self hosted the "problem" workspace.
In AdvancedLaunchTab#computeInitialCheckState()
  getModelKey(model) is returning null (plugin.getId() == null) for a 
WorkspaceFragmentModel that has a getFile() of 
L/org.eclipse.update.ui.win32/fragment.xml

So to test I would include the above fragment in the workspace.

Looks like the same problem here...double clicking to open a plugin manifest 
editor. IPluginModelBase#getPluginBase()#getId() is returning null.
